sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Execution of Suspicious File Type Extension
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects whether the image specified in a process creation event doesn't refer to an ".exe" (or other known executable extension) file. This can be caused by process ghosting or other unorthodox methods to start a process.
This rule might require some initial baselining to align with some third party tooling in the user environment.

signature_matches.name: linked against CPP regex library
signature_matches.description: linking/static/cppregex
match_data: regex_error(error_collate): The expression contained an invalid collating element name.
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: linked against CPP regex library
    namespace: linking/static/cppregex
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    references:
      - http://www.cplusplus.com/reference/regex/regex_error/
  features:
    - or:
      - string: "regex_error(error_syntax)"
        description: C++ STL regex library
      - string: "regex_error(error_collate): The expression contained an invalid collating element name."

signature_matches.name: contains PDB path
signature_matches.description: executable/pe/pdb
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: contains PDB path
    namespace: executable/pe/pdb
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    examples:
      - 464EF2CA59782CE697BC329713698CCC  # level32.exe
  features:

signature_matches.name: contain an embedded PE file
signature_matches.description: executable/subfile/pe
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: contain an embedded PE file
    namespace: executable/subfile/pe
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    mbc:
      - Execution::Install Additional Program [B0023]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-04.exe_:0x4060
  features:
    - or:
      - count(characteristic(embedded pe)): 1 or more
      - count(string(This program cannot be run in DOS mode.)): 2 or more

signature_matches.name: linked against ZLIB

    namespace: linking/static/zlib
    authors:

signature_matches.name: reference Base64 string
signature_matches.description: data-manipulation/encoding/base64
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: reference Base64 string
    namespace: data-manipulation/encoding/base64
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    att&ck:
      - Defense Evasion::Obfuscated Files or Information [T1027]
    mbc:
      - Data::Encode Data::Base64 [C0026.001]
      - Data::Check String [C0019]
    examples:
      - BFB9B5391A13D0AFD787E87AB90F14F5
      - 074072B261FC27B65C72671F13510C05
      - 5DB2D2BE20D59AA0BE6709A6850F1775
  features:
    - string: /ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/

signature_matches.name: compiled with rust
signature_matches.description: compiler/rust
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: compiled with rust
    namespace: compiler/rust
    authors:
      - "@_re_fox"
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    examples:
      - c3341b7dfbb9d43bca8c812e07b4299f:0x45F490
  features:
    - or:
      - substring: "run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable"
      - substring: "called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value"
      - substring: "called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value"
